  "text": "with Λ = {−2, −1, −0.5, 0.5, 1, 2}. x is a continuous explanatory variable, σ x is the standard deviation of x in the sample and λ is the parameter that determines the transformation. A particular value of λ implies a specific constant a λ . These constants are computed according to the suggestions made in [CITATION_1] and aim to make, for any given λ, the transformation as nonlinear as possible.",
